The explosion was heard all over the town and shattered windows on the neighboring streets.

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Nov. 21. -- Philadelphia has been well represented among the prize winners at the New-York Horse Show the past week. A.J. Cassatt of the Pennsylvania Railroad sent superb stock to the metropolis, and the Wideners of the Traction Company were well represented. Mr. P.A.B. Widener, by the bye, has a stable at Ogontz, near the city, that in fittings and furnishings is said to outrank anything of the kind in the country.

abstract: LONDON, Nov. 21. -- Mascagni's "Cavalleria Rusticana," which is being produced at Signor Lago's Shaftesbury Theatre, has proved to be as great a success in London as in the many other cities in which that short, but delightful, opera has been sung. There is no doubt that the attractiveness of the opera has been enhanced by the excellent rendering of Mascagni's music by the Shaftesbury orchestra, which is under the direction of Signor Arditi.
